Salary: Competitive salary plus fantastic company benefits
Ad Text:
Hello. We’re Virgin Australia.

We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way.

We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

What you’ll be doing

We’re looking for an Ancillary Product & Strategy Specialist to help us grow the products our guests love. This role sits within our Revenue Management team and reports to the Senior Manager, Ancillary Product & Strategy. You’ll be part of a team that’s shaping the future of our product portfolio – from strategy and performance reporting to proposition evolution and BAU product management.

You’ll work across the business to support the development of our 3-year product strategy and roadmap, dive deep into data to uncover insights, and help bring new ideas to life. You’ll also get to see the impact of your work every time you fly with us – because what you do will help make our guests’ experience even better.

You’ll be great in this role if you…

You’re a strategic thinker with a knack for turning data into stories that drive decisions. You’ve got experience in strategy, consulting or commercial analytics, and you’re comfortable working with ambiguity. You know your way around Excel and PowerBI, and you’re confident communicating with stakeholders at all levels.

You’re curious, collaborative, and love solving problems. You’re not afraid to challenge the status quo and bring fresh ideas to the table. And you care about doing things the right way – with integrity, attention to detail, and a focus on impact.

To be considered, you’ll need:

A relevant Bachelor’s degree
2+ years’ experience in strategy/management consulting or similar commercial analytics roles
Strong skills in data analysis, insight generation, and stakeholder communication
Advanced Excel and PowerBI (or similar tools)

What you’ll get from us

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)
A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs
One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road
Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide
Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services
Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health
‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you.

When everyone is included, everyone wins

We’re all individuals. And we love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQI+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.

Ready to apply?

We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues.​ We know work and life are intertwined. That’s why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high-performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.

Your New Role 

We have a 12-month max-term contract opportunity for a Technical Business Analyst to join the Enterprise Technology team and undertake technical analysis across Enterprise platforms, GRC, Data assets and assessment of new platforms. 

Key responsibilities will include;

Discover, identify and document data, integrations and platform impacts across different project workstreams. 

Liaise with project team members, business stakeholders and external vendors to document requirements, analyse impacts, and understand functional/non-functional implications. 

Actively engaging with Technology & Data SMEs and owners to analyse requirements and ensure solutions align with expected outcomes.

Provide support to business application in interpreting outcomes into technical requirements and user stories. 
Troubleshooting performance issues and provide solutions for optimisation.
Assist team members with testing of solutions, primarily UAT.

What You’ll Need   

Experience working in complex enterprise Technology & Data Environments.
A keen interest in exploring and understanding Data sets with a focus on delivering high quality business outcomes.
Strong experience in requirements gathering, gap analysis and business consulting.
Power BI expertise and visualisation skills highly advantageous
Experience in training AI/ML models through supervised/unsupervised and categorical/continuous learning methods.
Modern business analysis tooling.
Python coding experience.

Life at AustralianSuper 

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we’re happy to discuss what this looks like for you. 

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity.  We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know. 

What’s Next 

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results. 

Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.
